,Recommended,277460,11193237,"Posted: 11 July, 2014",all,AC11B,"I got this title for 99 cents and at that price this is an amazing game. I didn't expect it to be as grand and visually impressive as the Rome: Total War series, but it has it's own unique style and the smaller scale of units allows for a quicker pace and more action. The strategy gets progressively more advanced and is way more in-depth than what you see at first glance. The tutorials are rather boring but they provide some nice tips that will help you out later in the missions once the difficulty increases. For a game made in 2003 the presentation is quite good, and anyone who appreciates Roman History and the fall of the Republic will be satisfied with the story. Overall a great game and for less than a dollar it is worth a spot in anyone's library. Make sure to get the Mods Complex (just search the forums for instructions) to get the best compatibility with newer systems and also some nice extras."
,Recommended,277460,17283773,"Posted: 29 July, 2015",all,Livto Kabaz,"Good old RTS which I played a lot when I was younger. When I saw it in good discount, I had to grab it. And it was worth it, although mixed reviews and advertised Technical problems scared me a bit, game runs fine on mine Win7 HP and even on Win 10. The game itself is quite hard and unforgiving but still very entertaining when you do good moves. It mainly focuses on tactics, strategy and placement of units and there is still good variety of missions. I also like although you can't build your base etc. like in other RTS, but you can still build various siege weapons, guard towers and recruit new units in villages.  I also recommend getting great adittion Mod Complex, it adds new breath to this great old game."
,Not Recommended,277460,18567813,"Posted: 19 October, 2015",all,THiNK3R,"Game is unplayable due to serious complatability issues.I played this as a kid and was looking forward to some nostalgia for the $5 that it cost, but out of the gate you have to find the .exe file in the steamapps folder and set compatability to Windows XP Service Pack 2 AND always boot the game directly from the .exe file, never from the steam launcher to avoid blackscreen at startup. Then, in an actual mission you will STILL get a black screen after the cinematic. Alt+tabbing and restoring the window will bring the image back up. Then, in-game the map/unit info overlay glitches 80-90% of the time when a unit is selected, making framerate crawl and locking up the mouse, killing the game. I was able to play through one of the tutorial missions without problems after working at fixing this for 2-3 hours, and even then when I tried to start a regular campaign mission the overlay glitch prevented me from doing anything at all.Also, in terms of gameplay, you're limited to a relatively tight camera zoom, making things feel claustrophobic and making situational awareness sort of difficult.TL;DR don't buy this unless you're prepared to do some serious troubleshooting just to get the game to a place where it's playable."
